ery good or very effective.\nMickelson was hailed as the wonder boy of American golf...\nDr Williams describes it as a potential wonder drug.', '神奇的;奇妙的;有奇效的\n米克尔森被誉为美国高尔夫球界的神奇小子。\n威廉斯医生称其可能会成为特效药。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you say that someone or something is a nine-day wonder or a one-day wonder, you disapprove of the fact that they are attracting so much interest and attention, because you think that their popularity will only last for a very short time.\nHarry dismissed his old friend's speech as 'a nine-day wonder'...\nSome supernova researchers wondered if it might be just a nine-day wonder.", '昙花一现的人(或事物);惊艳一时的人(或事物)\n哈里对老朋友的讲话不屑一顾，称之“火不了多久”。\n有些超新星研究者怀疑，这可能只是昙花一现。'], ["PHRASE\nYou can say 'I wonder' if you want to be very polite when you are asking someone to do something, or when you are asking them for their opinion or for information.\nI was just wondering if you could help me...\nI just wonder what you make of all that...", '(用于礼貌地请人做事、征求意见或打听消息时)不知…，请问…\n不知您是否能帮我个忙。\n我只是纳闷儿你是怎么看待这一切的。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you say 'no wonder', 'little wonder', or 'small wonder', you mean that something is not surprising.\nNo wonder my brother wasn't feeling well...\nUnder such circumstances, it is little wonder that they experience difficulties...", '难怪；怪不得；不足为怪\n难怪我兄弟感觉不舒服了。\n在这种情形下，他们遇到困难就不足为怪了。'], ["PHRASE\nYou can say 'No wonder' when you find out the reason for something that has been puzzling you for some time.\nBrad was Jane's brother! No wonder he reminded me so much of her!", '（表示找出某事的原因）难怪，怪不得\n布拉德是简的兄弟！怪不得他老是让我想起她呢！'], ['PHRASE\nIf you say that a person or thing works wonders or does wonders, you mean that they have a very good effect on something.\nA few moments of relaxation can work wonders...\nRushton has done wonders for the industry.', '创造奇迹;产生奇迹\n放松一会儿就可以收到奇效。\n拉什顿创造了行业奇迹。']]}]